      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">52.202-1</ph> Definitions.</title>
      <conbody outputclass="clause" class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p id="d3047e8" class="- topic/p ">As prescribed
in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i1125324.dita#i1125324"
                     base="i1125324"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">2.201</xref>
            </ph>, insert the
following clause:</p>
         <p id="d3047e14" outputclass="Ctr_SmCaps" class="- topic/p "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-007?>
            <ph rev="FAC 2020-06 June 5, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">Definitions (Jun 2020)<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 52.202-1 by—
a. Revising the date of the clause;?></ph>
         </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">When a solicitation provision or contract clause uses a word
or term that is defined in the Federal Acquisition Regulation (FAR),
the word or term has the same meaning as the definition in FAR <xref href="FAR-i1125359.dita#i1125359"
                  base="i1125359"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref> in effect at the
time the solicitation was issued, unless-</p>
         <ol id="d3024e31" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d3047e27" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>The
solicitation, or amended solicitation, provides a different definition;</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d3047e32" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>The contracting
parties agree to a different definition;</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d3047e37" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>The part,
subpart, or section of the FAR where the provision or clause is
prescribed provides a different meaning; <ph rev="FAC 2020-06 June 5, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-007?> <?FM MARKER [Why] b. Removing the word “or” at the end of paragraph (c);?></ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d3047e46" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>The word
or term is defined in <ph rev="FAC 2020-06 June 5, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-007?>FAR <xref href="FAR-i1086363.dita#i1086363"
                           base="i1086363"
                           outputclass="fm:Part"
                           class="- topic/xref ">part  31</xref>,<?FM MARKER [Why] c. Removing from paragraph (d) “FAR Part” and “procedures.” and adding “FAR part” and “procedures; or” in their places, respectively; and?></ph> for use
in the cost principles and <ph rev="FAC 2020-06 June 5, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">procedures;
or</ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d3047e61" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2020-06 June 5, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-007?>The word or term defines an
acquisition-related threshold, and if the threshold is adjusted
for inflation as set forth in FAR <xref href="FAR-id1617MD00FX5.dita#id1617MD00FX5"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                           class="- topic/xref ">1.109</xref>(a), then the changed
threshold applies throughout the remaining term of the contract,
unless there is a subsequent threshold adjustment; see FAR <xref href="FAR-id1617MD00FX5.dita#id1617MD00FX5"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                           class="- topic/xref ">1.109</xref>(d).<?FM MARKER [Why] d. Adding paragraph (e).?></ph>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
         <p outputclass="Endofclause" class="- topic/p ">(End of clause)</p>
